title: Merge branch 'complex' into master
message:
Merge branch 'complex' into master

This commit signals that development of complex calculation has finally
been declared complete. There may still be issues, but my testing did not
find them, and the complex branch head is a working application that is
ready for production.

This merge therefore both signals that the complex build is the
authoritative production one, and merges the working application there
with the few upgrades made on master.

The results of this commit will be tested for correctness, any issues
found will be fixed, and the result, when satisfactory, will be deployed
to production as version 2.0

Signed-off-by: Ryan Hodin <ryan951357@gmail.com>

title: Squash commit for parseComplex
message:
Squash commit for parseComplex

This is a combination of 5 commits, containing the implementation of the
parseCoefficient processor. These commits were squashed so tools like
rebase would function properly.

The first commit's message is:
Properly comment parseComplex

Also start working on using parseCoefficient.

This commit doesn't work for numbers that include pi or e.

This is the 2nd commit message:

Add the simplest case for parseCoefficient processing

This is the 3rd commit message:

Add the second-simplest case

Also add some basic error checking to parseCoefficient, necessary for this

This is the 4th commit message:

Add two more simple cases

Also slightly change the code for the last one.

This is the 5th commit message:

Implement the last case

It should do, for the time being.

title: Add NaN check to double->string function
message:
Add NaN check to double->string function
This doesn't trap NaN's in functions that bypass inIntTermsOfAny(), which should be fairly rare.
This is also not a primary line of defense for NaN's, as it is preferable to have a more detailed error message, whose generation requires information only available at its generation.
Therefore, any time this error message appears should be recorded so that a check can be added to the operation to keep it from appearing again.

title: Redo error handling - Fixes #12
message:
Redo error handling - Fixes #12
Calculations which may result in errors are now performed in if/else trees, which allows visibility checks and so on to be performed regardless of error.
This fixes the root cause of #12, being that the calculate button was not set to be gone in the error condition

message:
Add support for -pi and -e - Fixes #4
This commit adds support in the string->number and in the number->string
methods for negative pi and negative e to be displayed as "-{pi}" and
"-e", rather than "-1{pi}" and "-1e", respectively.
